cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper focuses on compressing deep neural networks for mobile devices, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves merging multiple pre-trained models, which falls under the category of transfer learning and multi-task learning (cs.AI). The use of layer-wise neuron sharing and weight updating also suggests a potential application in neural architecture search (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments involve image datasets such as ImageNet and CelebA, indicating a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
